```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Define API endpoint for battle data
url = "api.historicalbattles.com/v1/battles"

# Retrieve battle data
battle_data = pd.read_json(url)

# Filter data for specific formations
cavalry_data = battle_data[battle_data["formation"] == "cavalry"]
infantry_data = battle_data[battle_data["formation"] == "infantry"]

# Analyze effectiveness of formations
cavalry_effectiveness = cavalry_data["victory"] / cavalry_data["num_cavalry"]
infantry_effectiveness = infantry_data["victory"] / infantry_data["num_infantry"]

# Create a scatter plot
plt.scatter(cavalry_effectiveness, infantry_effectiveness)
plt.xlabel("Cavalry Effectiveness")
plt.ylabel("Infantry Effectiveness")
plt.title("Effectiveness of Different Formations")
plt.show()

# Print results
print("The average effectiveness of the cavalry is:", cavalry_effectiveness.mean())
print("The average effectiveness of the infantry is:", infantry_effectiveness.mean())
```
